name: Patagonia
summary: Patagonia, the outdoor clothing and gear brand known for its environmental activism, is taking a unique approach to Black Friday. Instead of offering traditional sales, Patagonia is using the day to promote its "Anti-Black Friday" message, encouraging consumers to buy less and choose sustainable products. The company has long been vocal about climate change and has emphasized the importance of protecting the environment. Patagonia has also tightened its operations, which has drawn mixed reactions from workers, some of whom believe the company has lost its soul. Despite the controversy, Patagonia's Black Friday sales are still highly anticipated, with many retailers offering discounts on its popular items, such as the Nano Puff jacket.

name: Columbia
summary: Columbia University celebrated exceptional athletic achievements and holiday festivities. Michael Zheng became the first Columbia NCAA singles champion. Columbia and Dartmouth shared the Ivy League title in athletics. Columbia Mall prepared for the Black Friday shopping rush. The South Carolina Christmas Tree lighting ceremony commenced the holiday season at the State House. In sports, Indiana University beat Columbia in basketball with a double-double from Garzon. Despite being a long-time underdog, Columbia University's football team secured the Ivy League title for the first time in six decades. A rollover crash occurred in Columbia on Monday. The OMB proposed $7.3 billion in additional funding for Columbia and Virginia submarine construction. Columbia University also earned an Ivy League title in football, defeating Cornell 17-9.

name: Medrick Burnett Jr
summary: On November 26, 2022, Alabama A&M linebacker Medrick Burnett Jr. suffered a head injury during the Magic City Classic football game. Initially reported deceased, the university later retracted the statement, confirming Burnett was alive and in the hospital. Tragically, on December 27, 2022, Alabama A&M announced that Burnett had passed away at the age of 20, over a month after the incident. The news sparked widespread mourning and tributes to the young athlete, with condolences pouring in from the sports community and beyond.

summary: Ben Affleck and Jennifer Garner, who recently divorced, spent Thanksgiving together with their children. Affleck has been taking a break from filming to spend time with his family and is reportedly very happy with his life. Garner, who also spent Thanksgiving with her ex-husband, has been mourning the death of her beloved dog, Birdie. She has also written a tearful tribute to her former pet and spoken out about the importance of not marrying someone with the intention of changing them. Affleck and Garner's reunion on Thanksgiving was a sign of their continued friendship and commitment to co-parenting their children. Meanwhile, Garner is reportedly considering cutting ties with Affleck's new wife, Jennifer Lopez, unless their children are involved.
